1
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:13,567
They found survivors
on the other islands.

2
00:00:13,633 --> 00:00:15,400
Eden might be one of them.

3
00:00:15,467 --> 00:00:17,033
I need to do something.

4
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,300
I already ordered for him
to get a CT scan.

5
00:00:19,367 --> 00:00:22,367
We need to assess his condition
thoroughly.

6
00:00:22,433 --> 00:00:24,467
I know Red will come back
for us.

7
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:26,033
Eden, when will that happen?

8
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,500
I'm sure he'll come back for us.

9
00:00:27,567 --> 00:00:28,633
He's under sedation.

10
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:29,867
That's why he's asleep.

11
00:00:29,933 --> 00:00:32,400
We just have to observe him
within the next 72 hours.

12
00:00:32,467 --> 00:00:33,667
Thank you, Doc.

13
00:00:33,767 --> 00:00:35,800
You have to pay 10% interest
every month.

14
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:38,167
If you fail to pay
for two months,

15
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:39,767
I'll press charges against you.

16
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:42,100
One of the rescuers found it.

17
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:43,700
I can't be mistaken!

18
00:00:43,767 --> 00:00:45,367
Because I'm the one
who gave this to her.

19
00:00:45,433 --> 00:00:47,233
I'm begging you.

20
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:50,067
Let's go back to the island
where you found the survivors.

21
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:52,600
My daughter might be there, Sir!

22
00:00:52,667 --> 00:00:53,667
Yenyen.

23
00:00:53,733 --> 00:00:55,700
Yenyen, where are you?

24
00:00:55,767 --> 00:00:57,300
- Who is Yenyen?
- Where are you, Yenyen?

25
00:00:57,367 --> 00:00:59,600
I'm done waiting, Raichu!

26
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:02,267
He has already forgotten
his promise!

27
00:01:02,333 --> 00:01:04,233
I'm done!

28
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:05,500
I'm done waiting!

29
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:29,233
There's a boat!

30
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:32,667
It's Red!

31
00:01:32,733 --> 00:01:33,700
He came back!

32
00:01:35,067 --> 00:01:35,667
Raichu!

33
00:01:37,233 --> 00:01:38,200
Raichu!

34
00:01:39,467 --> 00:01:41,133
There's a boat.
Do you hear that?

35
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,400
Eden!

36
00:01:46,533 --> 00:01:48,367
It's my mom!

37
00:01:48,433 --> 00:01:50,100
Do you hear that?

38
00:01:50,167 --> 00:01:51,200
What are you talking about?

39
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:53,400
- It's my mom's voice!
- How can your mom be here?

40
00:01:53,467 --> 00:01:55,100
She's in jail, isn't she?

41
00:01:55,167 --> 00:01:56,767
I don't know. But someone's
yelling out my name!

42
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:58,400
There's a boat on the shore.

43
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:00,600
Eden!

44
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:03,233
OMG!

45
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:05,267
Eden, it's Red!

46
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,100
He came back for us.

47
00:02:07,167 --> 00:02:08,633
It's my mom's voice, Raichu.

48
00:02:10,733 --> 00:02:11,667
Yenyen!

49
00:02:11,733 --> 00:02:14,067
Ma'am, it doesn't seem like
somebody's here.

50
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:16,233
Maybe we should head back now.

51
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:19,000
I'm not heading back
without my daughter.

52
00:02:19,067 --> 00:02:20,367
Yenyen!

53
00:02:21,733 --> 00:02:24,100
You're just imagining it
because you miss your mom.

54
00:02:24,167 --> 00:02:26,067
No, we should go out there.

55
00:02:26,133 --> 00:02:27,367
Come on, let's look for it.

56
00:02:27,433 --> 00:02:28,700
- What?
- Let's go!

57
00:02:28,767 --> 00:02:29,967
Hurry!

58
00:02:32,267 --> 00:02:33,033
- Eden!
- Ma'am...

59
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:34,533
what if she's not
on this island?

60
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,433
We can only find out
if we look for her.

61
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:39,167
Eden!

62
00:02:39,233 --> 00:02:40,600
Who is Yenyen, Sabina?

63
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:47,233
She's the girl that was with us
on the island.

64
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,767
Do you know anything about her?

65
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:52,533
Is she still alive?

66
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:55,767
Well, I guess so, Auntie.

67
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:58,633
Actually, all of us
on that island got rescued.

68
00:03:01,367 --> 00:03:03,133
Red and I got separated
from them

69
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:06,633
because he had
an emergency case.

70
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:11,200
And I volunteered to accompany
him to this hospital.

71
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,200
Thank you.

72
00:03:14,267 --> 00:03:15,700
I hope Yenyen is fine.

73
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,567
I'd feel bad for her parents
if she didn't make it back.

74
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:27,000
We know how hard it is to lose
a child.

75
00:03:27,067 --> 00:03:29,000
Especially to her mom.

76
00:03:29,833 --> 00:03:31,167
It really is painful.

77
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:37,367
I hope she's reunited
with her family.

78
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:43,467
You know how important
family is, right?

79
00:03:44,667 --> 00:03:46,067
Right, Sabina?

80
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,567
Look! There's a boat!

81
00:03:54,733 --> 00:03:56,167
A boat!

82
00:03:56,233 --> 00:03:58,200
We're here!

83
00:03:58,267 --> 00:03:59,533
Hey!

84
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:01,400
We're here!

85
00:04:01,467 --> 00:04:02,367
Help!

86
00:04:02,433 --> 00:04:03,400
We're here!

87
00:04:03,467 --> 00:04:04,967
Help!

88
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:07,233
Where are they?

89
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:11,567
Look, there's a tent here.

90
00:04:11,633 --> 00:04:13,233
Someone's here!

91
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:19,600
Look, someone made fire here.

92
00:04:19,667 --> 00:04:21,433
They're still here.

93
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:22,667
Yenyen!

94
00:04:24,633 --> 00:04:26,000
Yenyen!

95
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:28,233
Dear!

96
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:32,167
Okay, Ma'am. Let's look for them
separately.

97
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:33,233
So we can find them faster.

98
00:04:34,267 --> 00:04:35,200
Come on.

99
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,333
Yenyen!

100
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:42,033
Red...

101
00:04:43,267 --> 00:04:44,733
be well.

102
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,000
Once you get better...

103
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:49,367
we'll spend a lot
of time together again.

104
00:04:51,367 --> 00:04:53,300
We'll be happy once again.

105
00:04:59,067 --> 00:05:01,233
You know life is too short
to be unhappy.

106
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,567
Auntie, Uncle...

107
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:10,733
I'll get going now.

108
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,500
I'll come back later.

109
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:14,100
Take care.

110
00:05:14,167 --> 00:05:15,267
I will.

111
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:16,633
I'll call your parents.

112
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:18,367
Thank you, Uncle.

113
00:05:18,433 --> 00:05:19,333
Bye.
Thank you.

114
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:30,067
Hon...

115
00:05:31,633 --> 00:05:35,300
I'm so happy now that Red
is here with us.

116
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,200
I can make it up to him now.

117
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:42,667
This is like his second life.

118
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:50,200
I will try to be the best mother
I can be to him. I promise.

119
00:05:55,167 --> 00:05:57,267
You will always be the best
mother for our son.

120
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:01,567
No...

121
00:06:03,433 --> 00:06:05,200
No.

122
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:08,133
I have had a lot
of shortcomings...

123
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:10,633
Hon...

124
00:06:14,733 --> 00:06:17,167
ever since Angelo died.

125
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:25,000
He's all I think about.
I've neglected you and Red.

126
00:06:25,067 --> 00:06:27,433
I'm just human.

127
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:28,667
I was in pain.

128
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:35,400
No one seemed to be on my side.

129
00:06:35,467 --> 00:06:38,000
I was in a lot of pain.

130
00:06:42,667 --> 00:06:44,000
I'm sorry.

131
00:06:45,667 --> 00:06:47,067
I'm so sorry.

132
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:53,100
I promise to make it up
to you and Red.

133
00:06:56,467 --> 00:06:57,300
I hope...

134
00:06:59,633 --> 00:07:01,167
I hope...

135
00:07:01,233 --> 00:07:03,233
I hope it's not too late.

136
00:07:05,533 --> 00:07:09,133
I hope we can still be
one happy family.

137
00:07:11,767 --> 00:07:12,933
Hon.

138
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:18,400
Now that Red is with us again...

139
00:07:20,267 --> 00:07:21,667
I think the pain will be less.

140
00:07:25,667 --> 00:07:27,000
We can heal together.

141
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,267
And we can be happy again.

142
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:33,300
Thank you, Hon.

143
00:07:35,167 --> 00:07:36,167
And I'm sorry.

144
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:39,267
I'm sorry.

145
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,633
Help!

146
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,067
Yenyen!

147
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:55,267
Yenyen!

148
00:08:06,167 --> 00:08:07,500
Eden!

149
00:08:07,567 --> 00:08:13,133
- Mom!
- Eden!

150
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:24,567
- Mom!
- Eden!

151
00:08:24,667 --> 00:08:27,000
You're alive!

152
00:08:35,233 --> 00:08:36,333
You're alive.

153
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:41,467
- Eden, you're alive.
- Mom!

154
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:45,567
- Mom!
- Eden!

155
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:55,700
I did nothing but pray
that we'll see each other again.

156
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:57,567
I want to be with you again.

157
00:08:57,633 --> 00:08:58,967
I prayed for you
to still be alive.

158
00:09:01,567 --> 00:09:06,400
You're the only reason
why I kept hanging on.

159
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,433
Mom.

160
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:19,200
This is unbelievable.

161
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:23,167
When I heard your voice,
I knew that it was you.

162
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,067
How did you get out of jail?

163
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:34,467
They granted our appeal.

164
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:36,533
I was acquitted.

165
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:39,733
Because you're innocent, Mom.

166
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:42,600
I know.

167
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:50,533
God answered all our prayers,
Dear.

168
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:55,200
Did you know how happy
I was when they released me?

169
00:09:55,267 --> 00:09:56,633
But...

170
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:58,533
the happiness went away

171
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,967
when I found out
what happened to you.

172
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:07,300
I thought I would never
see you again.

173
00:10:10,233 --> 00:10:12,033
Sorry.

174
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:15,633
I thought I would never
see you again, Mom.

175
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:17,367
Sorry Mom.

176
00:10:17,433 --> 00:10:21,333
- I'm always thinking of you.
- I do too.

177
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:24,233
I miss you every day, Mom.

178
00:10:28,367 --> 00:10:31,033
I know you worry
about me every day.

179
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:35,633
I don't know how to let you know
I'm safe.

180
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:43,333
Mom, you don't know what we've
been through on this island.

181
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:49,633
I missed you.

182
00:10:52,767 --> 00:10:55,500
From now on...

183
00:10:57,333 --> 00:10:59,533
I will take care of you
from now on.

184
00:11:01,467 --> 00:11:03,700
I will tend to your every need.

185
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:07,533
I'll do everything to make you
forget all the bad things

186
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:09,300
that happened here.

187
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:12,400
I will never leave you.

188
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:17,333
I will always be with you.

189
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:19,467
We'll create beautiful memories
together.

190
00:11:19,533 --> 00:11:20,700
Just the two of us.

191
00:11:24,733 --> 00:11:26,967
Thank you so much, Mom.

192
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:31,233
- Thank you so much.
- I never gave up.

193
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:36,000
I never gave up, especially...

194
00:11:37,533 --> 00:11:41,233
when I saw this.

195
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:43,100
One of the rescuers
gave this to me.

196
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:45,200
That's when I knew
that I needed to find you.

197
00:11:45,267 --> 00:11:47,333
I knew you were alive.

198
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:48,700
I need you.

199
00:11:48,767 --> 00:11:50,100
I never gave up, Dear.

200
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:53,100
I never lost hope.

201
00:11:54,667 --> 00:11:57,200
Thank you for not giving up.

202
00:11:57,267 --> 00:11:59,367
I will never give up.

203
00:11:59,433 --> 00:12:02,967
I will never ever give up
on you.

204
00:12:03,033 --> 00:12:06,433
- I love you so much, Mom.
- I love you so much.

205
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:10,333
I love you more than my life.

206
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,200
Eden...

207
00:12:23,167 --> 00:12:24,267
Excuse me.

208
00:12:26,733 --> 00:12:28,400
Can I join you guys?

209
00:13:02,367 --> 00:13:06,167
The doctor said you're okay.

210
00:13:06,233 --> 00:13:10,433
They put dextrose on you
because you're dehydrated.

211
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:12,433
But they said we could go home
anytime.

212
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,233
Your Aunt Dindi can't wait
to see you.

213
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:18,400
- Mom.
- Yes?

214
00:13:18,467 --> 00:13:22,000
I still can't believe
you're here with me.

215
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:26,033
It feels like a dream.

216
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:30,733
I want to hug you.

217
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:34,400
- I'm afraid to lose you again.
- My gosh.

218
00:13:34,467 --> 00:13:37,367
No, Dear. That won't happen
again.

219
00:13:40,533 --> 00:13:41,600
Get some rest.

220
00:13:41,667 --> 00:13:42,633
Stop moving too much.

221
00:13:50,367 --> 00:13:51,367
What's the matter?

222
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:58,067
I'm just thinking about the
person I was with on the island.

223
00:13:59,233 --> 00:14:00,100
Raichu?

224
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:07,233
Her parents picked her up
earlier.

225
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:10,067
She didn't get to say goodbye
because you were sleeping.

226
00:14:45,267 --> 00:14:47,633
Red?

227
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:49,267
Red, son.

228
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:51,133
How are you? How are you
feeling, Son?

229
00:14:53,433 --> 00:14:54,667
How do you feel?

230
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:57,667
Mom...

231
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:00,267
where am I?

232
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,533
How did I get here?

233
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:11,967
Calm down, calm down.

234
00:15:12,033 --> 00:15:13,033
You're still recovering.

235
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:17,733
Your wound might start
bleeding again.

236
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:19,667
Mom...

237
00:15:19,733 --> 00:15:20,667
Dad...

238
00:15:22,433 --> 00:15:24,400
I'm just so happy
that you're here.

239
00:15:29,767 --> 00:15:32,500
I'm so excited to see you again.

240
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:35,200
I thought...

241
00:15:36,433 --> 00:15:38,100
I was imagining things, but...

242
00:15:40,667 --> 00:15:42,633
but I can hold you now, Mom.

243
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:45,567
You're real.

244
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,067
I thought...

245
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:51,533
I thought I was going to die
on that island.

246
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,000
I thought...

247
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:55,067
I thought I would never
see you again.

248
00:15:55,133 --> 00:15:56,700
No, don't say that, Son.

249
00:15:58,167 --> 00:15:58,733
You know...

250
00:16:00,300 --> 00:16:01,900
God is so good.

251
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:05,167
He's so good.

252
00:16:05,233 --> 00:16:07,467
He will never let
that happen to us.

253
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:14,000
We still have a lot of plans
to travel abroad.

254
00:16:14,067 --> 00:16:16,600
You still have a lot
of dreams to fulfill.

255
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,933
We're always here for you, Son.
Okay?

256
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:24,400
I wanted to give up
so many times.

257
00:16:26,467 --> 00:16:28,133
I almost died.

258
00:16:30,633 --> 00:16:32,267
But whenever I thought
about you...

259
00:16:34,433 --> 00:16:36,933
whenever I looked at
your picture in my wallet...

260
00:16:39,767 --> 00:16:41,433
it made me want to fight.

261
00:16:44,633 --> 00:16:46,167
I don't want you to lose me...

262
00:16:47,833 --> 00:16:49,433
the way you lost Angelo.

263
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:54,267
You really are my son.

264
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:56,100
You're a fighter.

265
00:16:56,167 --> 00:16:56,967
You're brave.

266
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:01,900
But...

267
00:17:04,667 --> 00:17:06,167
if it wasn't
for this one person...

268
00:17:08,267 --> 00:17:10,333
I wouldn't have made it here.

269
00:17:12,433 --> 00:17:14,933
She gave me courage.

270
00:17:18,533 --> 00:17:19,400
I wonder where she is now.

271
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:24,667
I hope she was saved too.

272
00:17:26,733 --> 00:17:27,933
What is this?

273
00:17:43,733 --> 00:17:45,000
This bracelet...

274
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:48,667
he gave this to me.

275
00:17:50,667 --> 00:17:52,233
He is so kind.

276
00:17:54,233 --> 00:17:56,633
He took care of me
when we were on the island.

277
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:11,100
So, she's a good kid...

278
00:18:14,267 --> 00:18:16,100
from a good family.

279
00:18:28,233 --> 00:18:30,567
His parents raised him well.

280
00:18:39,467 --> 00:18:41,067
I want to meet her.

281
00:18:59,767 --> 00:19:03,667
I want to thank him personally
for helping you.

282
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:12,533
I will introduce her to you
the moment I see her again.

283
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:33,533
I'm sure you'll like him, Mom.

284
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,533
Once I meet him...

285
00:19:38,767 --> 00:19:42,333
he will be a part of our family.

286
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:54,500
And I will treat her
as my child.

287
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:07,167
I will treat him as my own.

288
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:32,767
Mom and I are heading back home,
Auntie.

289
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:35,233
We're just waiting
for my discharge slip.

290
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,333
I'm okay now.

291
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:41,467
I'm so excited to reunite
with you, guys.

292
00:20:41,533 --> 00:20:42,533
We'll go out together, okay?

293
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:43,767
We'll eat out.

294
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:45,633
My treat, Eden.

295
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:47,200
I like that!

296
00:20:49,267 --> 00:20:52,100
Can we bring Raichu along?

297
00:20:52,167 --> 00:20:55,033
I owe her big time.

298
00:20:55,100 --> 00:21:00,367
No matter where we are,
we always help each other.

299
00:21:00,433 --> 00:21:02,733
Raichu? Yes, you can bring her
along.

300
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:05,067
I'm going to work now.

301
00:21:05,133 --> 00:21:07,233
Okay, Auntie. Be safe.

302
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:13,000
And thank you for taking care
of my mom while I'm gone.

303
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:16,367
Of course! She's my one and only
sister whom I love so much.

304
00:21:16,433 --> 00:21:17,533
Bye, Auntie.

305
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,600
Take care.

306
00:21:23,533 --> 00:21:25,600
Mom...

307
00:21:25,667 --> 00:21:29,167
are we going straight home
once we get to Manila?

308
00:21:30,633 --> 00:21:31,767
Why?

309
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:34,533
I want to go somewhere first.

310
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,733
I have to take care
of something important.

311
00:21:39,067 --> 00:21:40,500
What is it?

312
00:21:40,567 --> 00:21:42,167
It's about Coach Vinluan.

313
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:48,133
I promised her I'd do this first
once I returned to Manila.

314
00:21:51,167 --> 00:21:52,633
I will give this
to her daughter.

315
00:21:56,567 --> 00:21:59,800
I feel bad about what happened
to her.

316
00:21:59,867 --> 00:22:03,133
I remember you were always
talking about her.

317
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:08,667
She was like your mother
at school, right?

318
00:22:08,733 --> 00:22:10,633
Too bad we didn't get to meet.

319
00:22:12,067 --> 00:22:14,567
I would like to personally
thank her

320
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:17,400
for all the kindness
she showed you.

321
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:21,167
Oh...

322
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,133
Coach...

323
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:27,067
thank you so much.

324
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:36,267
I owe you a lot for taking care
of Eden.

325
00:22:40,767 --> 00:22:41,967
Rest now.

326
00:22:44,633 --> 00:22:46,500
And...

327
00:22:46,567 --> 00:22:50,967
take my endless gratitude
with you...

328
00:22:52,300 --> 00:22:54,600
for all the love you gave Eden.

329
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:55,667
Coach...

330
00:23:57,700 --> 00:23:59,033
you're here now.

331
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:02,467
I brought you home.

332
00:24:05,267 --> 00:24:06,367
Let's go inside.

333
00:24:07,433 --> 00:24:09,600
Let's talk to her daughter.

334
00:24:17,567 --> 00:24:19,200
Here it is.

335
00:24:19,267 --> 00:24:22,000
Let me do it. Give it to me.

336
00:24:22,067 --> 00:24:25,967
Oh, and by the way, your friend
has been rescued too.

337
00:24:26,033 --> 00:24:27,467
Sabina told me earlier.

338
00:24:27,533 --> 00:24:29,500
What was her name again?

339
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:30,767
Yenyen?

340
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:31,967
Did they find her?

341
00:24:34,233 --> 00:24:37,200
Where is she? Do you have
information about her?

342
00:24:37,267 --> 00:24:38,533
Don't worry.

343
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:41,733
I talked to the airline's
management.

344
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:44,467
The rescued ones' information
is confidential,

345
00:24:44,533 --> 00:24:48,433
but they promised they'd do
something to help us out.

346
00:24:48,500 --> 00:24:49,300
Thanks, Dad.

347
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:53,600
I hope we'll find her soon.

348
00:24:56,367 --> 00:25:02,133
Dear, why are you holding on
to me too tight?

349
00:25:02,233 --> 00:25:03,367
But I like this.

350
00:25:03,433 --> 00:25:09,067
I felt so sad earlier

351
00:25:09,133 --> 00:25:10,300
when I talked to Miss Vinluan's
daughter.

352
00:25:10,367 --> 00:25:11,933
I feel bad that she lost
her mom.

353
00:25:13,333 --> 00:25:15,233
I can't imagine if that happened
to me.

354
00:25:15,300 --> 00:25:18,333
I can't bear it.

355
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:23,667
I'm so grateful and thankful
to God for having you.

356
00:25:23,733 --> 00:25:26,133
And we're not going
to waste any time.

357
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:32,200
I will take care of you
and give you a better future.

358
00:25:32,267 --> 00:25:33,367
Don't worry, Mom.

359
00:25:33,433 --> 00:25:35,333
I will help you out.

360
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:37,733
But you have to promise that
you won't neglect your studies.

361
00:25:37,833 --> 00:25:38,767
Because that's your priority.

362
00:25:38,833 --> 00:25:40,733
Of course.

363
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:44,533
Mom, I have to go
to the campus tomorrow.

364
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:46,700
We will have a tribute
for Miss Vinluan.

365
00:25:46,767 --> 00:25:48,500
I'm going to help them
with the preparations.

366
00:25:48,567 --> 00:25:53,067
Will I meet the guy who helped
you out on the island?

367
00:25:53,133 --> 00:25:55,033
What's his name again?

368
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:56,633
- Oh, you mean Red?
- Yeah, that guy.

369
00:25:57,600 --> 00:25:59,567
I'm hoping to see him.

370
00:26:00,767 --> 00:26:02,633
I wonder where he is.

371
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:05,067
Red and I are already here, Hon.

372
00:26:05,133 --> 00:26:07,367
Yes, let's just meet
at the restaurant.

373
00:26:07,433 --> 00:26:08,167
All right.

374
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:10,333
That was your dad.

375
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:12,300
We'll just meet him
at the restaurant.

376
00:26:12,367 --> 00:26:13,333
Okay.

377
00:26:24,067 --> 00:26:26,967
Red, it's so good to see you.

378
00:26:27,033 --> 00:26:30,567
Sab, where are Yenyen
and Raichu?

379
00:26:30,633 --> 00:26:32,100
Did you see them?

380
00:26:32,167 --> 00:26:33,667
What happened to them?

381
00:26:33,733 --> 00:26:35,033
I don't remember what happened.

382
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:39,100
I think Red sees Yenyen
more than a friend.

383
00:26:39,167 --> 00:26:41,267
Don't get ahead of yourself.

384
00:26:41,333 --> 00:26:45,533
For me, I'm happy as long
as our son is happy.

385
00:26:45,633 --> 00:26:48,067
She better not try touching
my daughter.

386
00:26:48,133 --> 00:26:50,567
Because I'm not afraid
to go back to jail

387
00:26:50,633 --> 00:26:53,467
if she tries to hurt Eden.

388
00:26:53,533 --> 00:26:57,633
Coach used to say that good
people are like candles.

389
00:26:57,700 --> 00:27:01,133
They burn themselves up
to give light to others.

390
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,600
We'll find what we're looking
for in the light.
